verbose_text: Located at the non reducing end of glycans comprised of glycoproteins (N- and O linked) and glycolipids, alpha3 fucosylated oligosaccharides form the Lewis related carbohydrate antigen family (i.e. Le x, Le y and Sialyl-Le x), one of the major components of cell surface oligosaccharides.
evidence: reducing end of glycans comprised of glycoproteins (N- and O-linked) and glycolipids, alpha3
